01/11/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- A total of 9,726 foreign and domestic monitors will observe the 7 November referendum on Macedonia's new decentralisation laws -- twice the number of observers deployed for the last presidential and parliamentary elections, according to the State Electoral Commission.
In other news, Macedonia and Montenegro have signed an agreement on co-operation in the fight against money laundering. 
Podgorica also has sealed such accords with Belgrade and Tirana. 
(Utrinski Vesnik - 01/11/04; MIA - 30/10/04)
